                    "text": "When a phoenix dies, it collapses into a pile of smoldering ashes before returning to life fully healed 1d4 rounds later, as if subject to a 7th-level <a aonid=\"20\" game-obj=\"Rituals\"><i>resurrect</i></a> ritual. Self-resurrection happens only if there are some remains to resurrect; for instance, a phoenix killed by a <a aonid=\"76\" game-obj=\"Spells\"><i>disintegrate</i></a> spell can\u2019t use this ability. A phoenix whose remains rest within an area devoted to an evil deity by <a aonid=\"8\" game-obj=\"Rituals\"><i>consecrate</i></a> can\u2019t self-resurrect until its remains are no longer in that area. A phoenix can self-resurrect only once per year."
